displayName: Forest of Spirits - Enemy Leader's Chamber

parameters:
Kokuyou Tengu: "Grrr! Is Masaki with you? I thought you
might come!"

Masaki: "How dare you break into my home while I was away!
The spirit energy you stole from me when you attacked has
mostly recovered. Now it's time for payback for what
happened half a year ago!"

Senbi: "Guhuhu! Really? Your true spirit energy doesn't seem
to be there... Do you think you can defeat me now that I've
obtained the power of an oni?"

Masaki: "Hmph... How pitiful to have fallen so low as to
become an oni... And you think you can call yourself the
king of spirits after defeating me?"

Senbi: "Choosing any means necessary to become stronger is
my creed. What you're looking for is this sword, isn't it?"

Karin: "...! Is that the divine weapon for slaying oni--the
Sanmyouken?!"
Masaki: "Yes...? It's not rusted at all...?"

Oei: "Ugh! Didn't I tell you before we came here? Since it
was left in the treasury, it might be rusted..."

Senbi: "I was relieved to hear it was called a divine weapon
for slaying oni, but it's just a rusty piece of junk that
couldn't even cut a radish. Sky Fox Masaki--I will defeat
you here and become the new king of spirits! Guhahahahaha!"

Masaki: "Hah! You brutish dog, getting all cocky! You'll be
turned to cinders by my signature technique, Tenpa Raitei!"

Masaki: "Nuhahaha! How about that, Senbi! Paralyzed and
can't do anything, can you? As a mercy, I'll finish you off
with one blow."

Karin: "Yay! Masaki-chan's lightning strike was a direct
hit!"

Kachou: "As expected of someone who claims to be the king of
spirits, such an incredible technique. It's even more
powerful than when we saw it inside the coastal cave!"

Masaki: "Nyahaha! At that time, we were deep underground in
a cave! In this temple close to the sky, I can unleash even
greater power! We'll have to repair the roof later!"

Karin: "--! Master! Don't let your guard down! That
technique didn't work on Senbi!"

Senbi: "Guhuhuhu! Such a level of lightning strike won't
leave a single scratch on my skin!"

Masaki: "--!? Why are you laughing?! Could it be--my
technique--?!"

Karin: "No way...! Unbelievable! Senbi is absorbing Masaki-
chan's lightning strike?!"

Senbi: "Hundreds of years ago, when I was still a beast
spirit--I decided to make your lightning strike my own after
being defeated by you."

Senbi: "I've been storing and increasing a flame-like spirit
energy similar to your lightning within my body bit by bit,
and have sublimated it into my own technique--like this--!!"
Karin: "Uwahh!? Senbi released a lightning strike too?!"

Masaki: "~~~~!! Impossible...! (So Senbi had such
potential?)"

Senbi: "Surprised? Your techniques are ineffective against
me who has consumed them. The spirit energy I absorbed when
I attacked you half a year ago has been transformed into my
flesh and blood, and further evolved into nourishment! Hence
the name [Beast Lightning Oni Senbi]!"

Masaki: "...I apologize, everyone. It seems my favored
lightning strikes no longer affect that creature. I'm
ashamed I can't be of help even though I've become your
companion..."

Kachou: "Even if lightning is ineffective, we still have our
sword techniques. Please support us with your assistance.
Momiji, I'm counting on you for healing."
Momiji: "Yes. Let's all do our best together--"

Senbi: "So, are you ready for battle? Have you prepared
yourselves for the journey of death?"

Karin: "We can't afford to lose here! Come at us, Senbi!
We'll show you the power of us four!"

Senbi: "Don't make me laugh! I'll turn this temple into your
gravestone! My ultimate technique, Swift Thunder Beast Claw
Unrivaled--I'll carve it into every single one of your
cells!"

Ooooh--!? To be pushed back by a mere human girl...
Impossible!?
This is the end for you, Senbi! Yaaaahhh~~!!

Guaaaaah!! Ridiculous! To think that I, who have become a
War Oni, could lose...!

Senbi... no, Thousand Wolves. I admire your obsession with
strength. However, this is where your journey ends.
Grrrrr--! Masaki... I'll take you to hell with me!

Your demonic energy has already been depleted. Farewell,
Senbi--

A fox's funeral pyre. Let my flames send you off to the
heavens at least--

Gufufu... The Demon King I've chased for hundreds of
years... was never an opponent I could surpass...

Phew, haa... That was the toughest enemy we've faced so far,
but I'm glad we were able to defeat him. Thank you,
everyone.

We've experienced many battles and have become stronger than
before. Even a War Oni is not an unbeatable foe for us.

Three War Oni remain--let's keep up this momentum and win
through to the end.

Indeed. I now have a personal grudge after they invaded my
home. Those barbaric oni must be punished.

My my... I came to check on the Forest of Spirits and it
seems Senbi has been defeated as well.

I am Gyouon, one of the Eight Grudge War Oni. I've always
been by Kotaro-dono's side, so this is the first time I'm
speaking directly with you ladies.

You're the one who fanned the flames of Senbi's ambition and
lured him onto the path of oni, aren't you? How dare you
meddle so carelessly in our world of spirits!

Haha, Senbi wanted to defeat you. In exchange for joining
us, I shared with him the flesh of an oni.

Momiji-dono, your father Kotaro-dono was furious that you
turned against us. It's not too late to rejoin our ranks. We
would welcome you back.

...The time cannot be turned back. Please tell my father
that Momiji will defeat all of you--

What a shame. Well then, I suppose I'll take my leave for
today.

How cruel to strike without warning! What's wrong, little
ninja girl?

I remember now! Your face, I knew I had seen it somewhere
before... You know about the one-eyed giant oni, don't you!?

Ah, you mean Nyuudou? Due to his large size, it's not easy
to bring him along casually, so you shouldn't have met him
before... Hmm...?

Ten years ago, a village was slaughtered by a one-eyed giant
oni in Kai's Yugiri Village. At that time, you were with
that one-eyed oni!

I am the sole survivor of that village! I will avenge my
family and fellow villagers! I'll kill you right here!

Oh dear, did you have such a past? I'm sorry, I don't
remember. It's not the first or second time we've burned
down villages unnoticed--

Please remember. Something earth-shattering will happen soon
--if there's an opportunity then, I shall entertain you. My
mission is to collect grudges, after all

Wait! Are you running away, coward! I cannot rest until I
have avenged my village! Fight me!

Hehe, being scorned is also part of this humble monk's
duties. After all, being disliked is the role of a demon--
now if you'll excuse me--
--Gyun laughed as he vanished from sight!

Yugiri-chan, you mentioned it before. You became a ninja to
defeat the demon that attacked your hometown, right?
Is that Gyun the nemesis Yugiri-san has been searching for?

There's no mistake... He was with the one-eyed demon. I will
definitely be the one to defeat him...

Hmm, revenge is important, but fighting back-to-back battles
when you're low on energy is dangerous. We should head back
to Edo for now, especially since we've obtained the sword we
were after.

This sword... It's really rusted from top to bottom... I
wonder if the story about it being a divine weapon for
slaying demons is just a lie?

It's alright. With this level of rust, if we ask a skilled
sharpener to polish it, I believe it will shine brightly
once again.

Right. Once we return to Edo, I'll ask a blacksmith to take
a look at it.

Yugiri-chan, let's head back to Edo. The people of Iga Ninja
are probably waiting for your return.

...Ah. I apologize for losing my temper. If it gets fully
dark, the journey back will be difficult. Let's hurry out of
the Forest of Spirits.

Well then! After all this fighting, I'm starving. Let's have
some night soba on the way back! And add some fried tofu to
it
--Karin and the four set off on their return journey to Edo.

--Health and skill power have been \c[24]fully
restored\c[0]!
